      • makeImageCaptureOnFinish

        public StepAction<T> makeImageCaptureOnFinish()
        Marks that it is needed to produce a BufferedImage after invocation of Consumer.accept(Object) on this object. This image is produced by Captor.getData(java.lang.Object)

        NOTE 1

        This image is produced if there is any subclass of ImageCaptor or Captor that may produce a BufferedImage.

        NOTE 2

        A subclass of ImageCaptor or Captor should be able to handle input values T on success/on failure.
        Specified by:
